2001-08-06 10:22  bagder

	* lib/sendf.c:	 Jonathan Hseu noticed that you couldn't get a
	  header callback unless you
	    set CURLOPT_WRITEHEADER to non-NULL, even if you didn't care
	  about that
	    data. This is now fixed.

